{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"SVG Tutorial","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/SVG/Tutorial","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","sidebarHTML":"","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p>Scalable Vector Graphics, <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/SVG\">SVG</a>, is a W3C XML dialect to mark up graphics. It is partially implemented in Firefox, Opera, WebKit browsers, Internet Explorer and other browsers.</p>\n<p>This tutorial aims to explain the internals of SVG and is packed with technical details. If you just want to draw beautiful images, you might find more useful resources at <a href=\"https://inkscape.org/learn/\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">Inkscape's documentation page</a>. Another good introduction to SVG is provided by the W3C's <a href=\"https://www.w3.org/Graphics/SVG/IG/resources/svgprimer.html\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">SVG Primer</a>.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"introducing_svg_from_scratch","title":"Introducing SVG from Scratch","isH3":false,"content":"<ul>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/SVG/Tutorial/Introduction\">Introduction</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/SVG/Tutorial/Getting_Started\">Getting Started</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/SVG/Tutorial/Positions\">Positions</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/SVG/Tutorial/Basic_Shapes\">Basic Shapes</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/SVG/Tutorial/Paths\">Paths</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/SVG/Tutorial/Fills_and_Strokes\">Fills and Strokes</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/SVG/Tutorial/Gradients\">Gradients</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/SVG/Tutorial/Patterns\">Patterns</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/SVG/Tutorial/Texts\">Texts</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/SVG/Tutorial/Basic_Transformations\">Basic Transformations</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/SVG/Tutorial/Clipping_and_masking\">Clipping and masking</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/SVG/Tutorial/Other_content_in_SVG\">Other content in SVG</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/SVG/Tutorial/Filter_effects\">Filter effects</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/SVG/Tutorial/SVG_fonts\">SVG fonts</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/SVG/Tutorial/SVG_Image_Tag\">SVG Image tag</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/SVG/Tutorial/Tools_for_SVG\">Tools for SVG</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/SVG/Tutorial/SVG_and_CSS\">SVG and CSS</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>The following topics are more advanced and hence should get their own tutorials.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"scripting_svg_with_javascript","title":"Scripting SVG with JavaScript","isH3":false,"content":"<p>TBD</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"svg_filters_tutorial","title":"SVG filters tutorial","isH3":false,"content":"<p>TBD</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"animations_with_smil_in_svg","title":"Animations with SMIL in SVG","isH3":false,"content":"<p>TBD</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"creating_fonts_in_svg","title":"Creating fonts in SVG","isH3":false,"content":"<p>TBD</p>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Introducing SVG from Scratch","id":"introducing_svg_from_scratch"},{"text":"Scripting SVG with JavaScript","id":"scripting_svg_with_javascript"},{"text":"SVG filters tutorial","id":"svg_filters_tutorial"},{"text":"Animations with SMIL in SVG","id":"animations_with_smil_in_svg"},{"text":"Creating fonts in SVG","id":"creating_fonts_in_svg"}],"summary":"Scalable Vector Graphics, SVG, is a W3C XML dialect to mark up graphics. It is partially implemented in Firefox, Opera, WebKit browsers, Internet Explorer and other browsers.","popularity":0.0065,"modified":"2022-09-09T07:06:10.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"Tutorial de SVG","locale":"es","native":"Español"},{"title":"Tutoriel SVG","locale":"fr","native":"Français"},{"title":"SVG教本","locale":"ja","native":"日本語"},{"title":"SVG 튜토리얼","locale":"ko","native":"한국어"},{"titl